<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-070-420  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 070 420.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Banking  Feb 1989 v6 n2 p24(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Program uses PCs to automate forms completion. (Software Review)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Persing, Linda L.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>FormFiller from BLOC Publishing is designed to automate formcompletion so that people can use a microcomputer to fill in theblanks of any preprinted form.andP;  The $149.95 program includesbuilt-in routines to detect errors or omissions in designatedfields.andP;  It features over 40 mathematical, financial and logicalfunctions similar to those in spreadsheets.andP;  FormFiller also hassome import-export capabilities and can look up data from aspecific table to fill in selected fields automatically.andP;  Theprogram's flaws include inadequate documentation but an upgradeversion, Version 2.0, which is scheduled for release in Feb 1989,should take care of this and other problems.andP;  Use of Formfillerrequires a thorough awareness of the form being filled up andpatience in learning operational concepts but it could potentiallybe an essential office tool.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bloc Publishing Corp. (products).andO;Product:   FormFiller (Data entry software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSoftware PackagesForms DesignOffice Automation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>